Euro Pares Losses Against Yen, U.S. Dollar as Asian Shares Erase Decline

-- B y   R o c k y   S w i f t
-- 
2011-02-28T04:01:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/euro-pares-losses-against-yen-u-s-dollar-as-asian-shares-erase-decline.html
The euro pared losses against the
yen and dollar as Asian shares erased a decline, reviving demand
for riskier assets.  The euro was at 112.28 yen as of 1 p.m. in Tokyo, after
earlier falling to 111.96, the weakest since Feb. 8. The shared
currency traded at $1.3746 from $1.3754 on Feb. 25.  The MSCI Asia Pacific Index of shares increased 0.1
percent, reversing a 0.5 percent decline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rocky Swift in Tokyo at 
